abstract: The U.S. government is overhauling parts of the nation's transplant system to make sure organs from the dead no longer go to waste — and to make it easier for the living to donate.
snippet: The U.S. government is overhauling parts of the nation's transplant system to make sure organs from the dead no longer go to waste — and to make it easier for the living to donate.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The U.S. government is overhauling parts of the nation's transplant system to make sure organs from the dead no longer go to waste — and to make it easier for the living to donate.
headline_main: US Proposes New Rules to Increase Organ Transplants
headline_print_headline: US Proposes New Rules to Increase Organ Transplants

abstract: WASHINGTON — Construction of new homes rose again in November while applications for building permits rose to the highest level in 12 years, both encouraging signs of a rebound in the housing market.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Construction of new homes rose again in November while applications for building permits rose to the highest level in 12 years, both encouraging signs of a rebound in the housing market.
headline_main: US Housing Construction Increases 3.2% in November
headline_print_headline: US Housing Construction Increases 3.2% in November

abstract: We need a broad national effort to recruit volunteers to educate and counsel the incarcerated.
snippet: We need a broad national effort to recruit volunteers to educate and counsel the incarcerated.
lead_paragraph: Decades after the prison population began its growth surge, criminal justice reform has finally moved into the national conversation.

abstract: Rudy Giuliani, the president's personal attorney, is now openly admitting that he pushed President Donald Trump to dismiss the former ambassador to Ukraine — a key factor in the Democrats' impeachment case against his boss.
snippet: Rudy Giuliani, the president's personal attorney, is now openly admitting that he pushed President Donald Trump to dismiss the former ambassador to Ukraine — a key factor in the Democrats' impeachment case against his boss.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Rudy Giuliani, the president's personal attorney, is now openly admitting that he pushed President Donald Trump to dismiss the former ambassador to Ukraine — a key factor in the Democrats' impeachment case against his boss.
headline_main: Giuliani Brags About Forcing Out Trump's Ukraine Ambassador
headline_print_headline: Giuliani Brags About Forcing Out Trump's Ukraine Ambassador

abstract: Democrats in the U.S. House of Representatives on Tuesday unveiled a bill that aims to zero out emissions from drilling, mining and other activities on federal land and waters by 2040, and puts the brakes on oil and gas leasing for at least a year.
snippet: Democrats in the U.S. House of Representatives on Tuesday unveiled a bill that aims to zero out emissions from drilling, mining and other activities on federal land and waters by 2040, and puts the brakes on oil and gas leasing for at least a year...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Democrats in the U.S. House of Representatives on Tuesday unveiled a bill that aims to zero out emissions from drilling, mining and other activities on federal land and waters by 2040, and puts the brakes on oil and gas leasing for at least a year.
headline_main: Democrats Aim for Net-Zero Emissions on Public Land by 2040
headline_print_headline: Democrats Aim for Net-Zero Emissions on Public Land by 2040

abstract: The U.S. House of Representatives will vote this week on whether to impeach President Donald Trump on charges that he abused the power of his office and obstructed Congress in its investigation of his dealings with Ukraine.
snippet: The U.S. House of Representatives will vote this week on whether to impeach President Donald Trump on charges that he abused the power of his office and obstructed Congress in its investigation of his dealings with Ukraine.

abstract: A federal judge sentenced U.S. President Donald Trump's former deputy campaign chairman Rick Gates to serve an intermittent term of 45 days in jail and 36 months of probation, saying that while she was moved by his extensive cooperation with prosecutors, she still felt some punishment was in order.
snippet: A federal judge sentenced U.S. President Donald Trump's former deputy campaign chairman Rick Gates to serve an intermittent term of 45 days in jail and 36 months of probation, saying that while she was moved by his extensive cooperation with prose...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A federal judge sentenced U.S. President Donald Trump's former deputy campaign chairman Rick Gates to serve an intermittent term of 45 days in jail and 36 months of probation, saying that while she was moved by his extensive cooperation with prosecutors, she still felt some punishment was in order.
headline_main: Judge Sentences Ex-Trump Campaign Aide Gates to Probation and 45 Days in Jail
headline_print_headline: Judge Sentences Ex-Trump Campaign Aide Gates to Probation and 45 Days in Jail

abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump is expected to be impeached on Wednesday when the Democratic-led House of Representatives votes on charges stemming from his effort to pressure Ukraine to investigate political rival Joe Biden.
snippet: U.S. President Donald Trump is expected to be impeached on Wednesday when the Democratic-led House of Representatives votes on charges stemming from his effort to pressure Ukraine to investigate political rival Joe Biden.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - U.S. President Donald Trump is expected to be impeached on Wednesday when the Democratic-led House of Representatives votes on charges stemming from his effort to pressure Ukraine to investigate political rival Joe Biden.
headline_main: Explainer: How Trump's Impeachment Trial Would Differ From a Criminal One
headline_print_headline: Explainer: How Trump's Impeachment Trial Would Differ From a Criminal One
